$interpreted: Rune: What is...Sophie doing?
Sophie: I'm combing your hair. It's so long~ Doesn't it get in your eyes?
Rune: ...Yes...but master...doesn't say to...tie it. No one...taught me.
Sophie: Well then, I'll just have to be your teacher~ Ask me whenever you want. But let me tell you, I'm strict~
Sophie: Rune?
Rune: No one...taught me...how to be...free...
Sophie: ......
Sophie: Well, there's nothing wrong with starting now~
Sophie: Readyyyyyy~ Here he is!
Ru-yi: Wow! What a stud!!
Hanbei: Well, at least now he looks human...
Sophie: Everybody, listen up~ Starting from today, Rune and Sanchez are no longer slaves. Let's hear it for...
Sophie: ...Wait a sec. Sanchez?
Rune: I saw him. He's...there.
Sanchez: Wai..wai..wait...I can walk myself! Ouch!!
Sanchez: Ahhhhhh! My butt hurts ~~
Rune: Sanchez...is free.
Sanchez: Oh yeah? Then let me walk around freely!!!
Sanchez: What is this anyway? I'm not as welcome, is that it?
Sophie: Sanchez, let everybody congratulate you~ The star of the show ought to be higher up than the rest of us...Hutchinson!
Sanchez: Wahhhh!!! Let me down! I'm afraid of heights!
Hutchinson: Please sir, don't be nervous. I'm just going to circle you around the tent.
Sanchez: You're all just picking on me! Help, help!!!
Sophie: Rune, now that you're free, what do you want to do?
Rune: I don't know...Lazer said...what you want...is the future. But now...I still...don't have...
Sophie: Don't worry. Come on everybody, let's say what we want to do. That way Rune will have a reference point~
Ru-yi: Okay, who is going to take the first swing?
Hutchinson: As for this...I...well...
Hanbei: Hey! Why are you all looking at me?
Hutchinson: Well, you're the oldest. We must respect our elders~
Ru-yi: That's right! The oldest member of Morgan's Marvelous Circus!
Hanbei: You brats! Call me old one more time! You'll never learn! Hmph!
Sophie: Hey, can't blame 'em. You are the oldest...
Hanbei: Hmph! Well, let me think...I want to see Sophie do something wrong for once!
Rune: Sophie...wrong?
Hanbei: People eventually make a mistake if they live long enough.
Hanbei: I made a promise to Morgan that I'd stay in the circus until the day Sophie's heart hardens.
Sophie: Okay, I get it. Come off it now~
Hutchinson: Jeezers! Doing good for you without you knowing it, what a gentleman~
Sophie: Hehe, well that'll never happen. So you're never leaving! Hutchinson? Maybe you'd like to be the most well-mannered Deer demi-human?
Hutchinson: Let's just say I'd like to be the greatest gentleman in the world, not just amongst the Deers! Ru-yi?
Ru-yi: ...I just want my belly button fixed. I hate that it spouts out water!
Ru-yi: Even though I'm happy in the circus...I just want to be a normal Whale...
Sophie: I've said it a million times. You're all "normal"! Whoever thinks otherwise is the one with the problem!
Sophie: Next time you say that I'm gonna——
Ru-yi: Do what?
Sophie: ——Tickle you to death!
Ru-yi: Wahahaha~ St..stoppp! ~ SopHIE!!! Okay, okay I won't say it!
Sophie: That's a good girl. Elio...what about you?
Elio: Me? Do I have to?
Sophie: Give it a try~ That way maybe we can help! Come on everybody, whaddaya say?
Hutchinson: Sophie is right. As a gentleman, helping others to achieve their dreams is very important.
Hutchinson: Come on, tell us! Elio?
Elio: ...There's nothing I want to do.
Rune: Elio...is like...me?
Elio: No, I just...
Hanbei: Oh, you don't want to say. What a rude, awk...
Sophie: Hanbei!
Sophie: Elio...are you okay?
Elio: Thanks, Sophie. It's okay.
Elio: Sophie? What's wrong?
Sophie: Elio...I'm sorry.
Elio: Sorry...why do you need to say sorry?
Sophie: Hanbei shouldn't have said that...he didn't mean anything by it...but it was still wrong.
Elio: ...Don't worry. He's not entirely wrong.
Sophie: I don't mean to make you more uncomfortable...but I still think that if you are willing to share it with us...
Elio: I don't want to cause you all any more trouble.
Sophie: But seeing you like this...it's even worse!
Sophie: Elio, I hope you feel happier soon. I'm not sure what's bothering you, but I just want to make you happy.
Elio: ...I'm just a stranger. I don't even really know you. What do you care about me?
Sophie: Because...
Sophie: Because...I like you!
Sophie: The first time I saw you, I liked you.
Sophie: My father taught me that if you want to save somebody, you must really like them! So, I——
Elio: ...Do I look so miserable that I need to be saved?
Sophie: No, no...it's not like that! I'm just saying! I hope I can be by your side and help you do what you want to do.
Sophie: I don't feel sorry for you or anything!
Elio: Sophie...
Sophie: You're right. It's not about you and this circus. It's that I like you. I just wanted you to hear it from me.
Sophie: I just don't know...if you're willing to let me help you.
Elio: Thanks, Sophie...I'm sorry.
Rune: Without...a command...what...should I do?
Sophie: Rune!
Sophie: Rune, have you seen Elio?
Rune: No...Elio.
Sophie: He's not here either...where'd he go to?
Rune: Sophie is...worried.
Sophie: ...Elio didn't come home last night. I can't find him anywhere.
Rune: Huh?
Sophie: Rune, I...I...I think Elio's missing!
